
Datatypes

    byte -128 -> 127
        default value = 0
    Ex:
    byte number = 10;

    short -32,768 -> 32,767
    default value = 0
    Ex:
    short number 450;

    int - 2,147,483,648 -> 2,147,483,647
    default value = 0
    Ex:
    int number = 9999;

    long -9,223,372,036,854,775,808 -> 9,223,372,036,854,775,807
    default value = 0
    Ex:
    long number 10L;

    float 32-bit IEEE 754
    Default value is 0.0f
    Ex:
    float number 924.2f;

    double 64-bit IEEE 754
    default value 0.0d;
    Ex:
    double number 2.2d;

    boolean true, false;
    default value false
    Ex:
    isEnabled = true;

    char
    Minimum value is '\u0000' (or 0)
    Maximum value is '\uffff' (or 65,535 inclusive)
    Ex:
    char letter = 'A';

    String
    Ex:
    String name = "Rukie";


 Access Modifiers:
    public
    private
    protected
    default

    static

11/10:

  Scanner class

  Allows user to enter input value

  Integer value:
  scanner.nextInt();

  String value:
  scanner.nextLine();

  Operators in java
  prefix
    ++var;
  postfix
    var++;
  comparison
    <, >, <=, >=
  multiplicative
    * / %
